.TH "blk_mangle_minor" 9 "blk_mangle_minor" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_mangle_minor \- scatter minor numbers apart
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" blk_mangle_minor
.BI "(int minor "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "minor" 12
minor number to mangle
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Scatter consecutively allocated \fIminor\fP number apart if MANGLE_DEVT
is enabled.  Mangling twice gives the original value.
.SH "RETURN"
Mangled value.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Don't care.
